1600.name: Kasha Bear Claw
1600.description: A claw pulled out from a kasha bear after killing it. Collect 5 of these.

1601.name: Kasha Blade Spider Talon
1601.description: A talon pulled out from a kasha blade spider after killing it. Collect 5 of these.

1602.name: Scarlet Salamander Scale
1602.description: A scale of a scarlet salamander. Collect 5 of these.

1603.name: Fiery Spirit Scroll
1603.description: The first scroll containing secret of kabart, the Orcs' traditional martial arts.

1604.name: Rosheek's Letter
1604.description: A letter written by Khavatari Rosheek. Take this to Gantaki Zu Urutu.

1605.name: Gantaki's Letter of Recommendation
1605.description: Gantaki's letter of recommendation. Receive the help of Gatekeeper Tamil and take this recommendation to Prefect Kasman in the Village of Gludin.

1606.name: Fig
1606.description: A fig given by Prefect Kasman. Take this to Khavatari Toruku.

1607.name: 4th Leather Pouch
1607.description: A leather pouch given by Khavatari Toruku. Take this, kill fighters of various races and collect 12 tokens.

1608.name: 4th Leather Pouch (Full)
1608.description: A full pouch of 12 tokens after killing fighters of various races. Take this to Khavatari Toruku.

1609.name: Vuku Orc Tusk
1609.description: A tusk obtained after killing a vuku Orc. Gather 3 of these.

1610.name: Ratman Fang
1610.description: A fang from a dead ratman fighter. Gather 3 of these.

1611.name: Langk Lizardman Tooth
1611.description: A tooth obtained after killing a Langk lizardman. Gather 3 of these.

1612.name: Felim Lizardman Tooth
1612.description: A tooth obtained after killing the Felim lizardman. Gather 3 of these.

1613.name: Iron Will Scroll
1613.description: The second scroll that contains secret of the Orcs' traditional martial arts, Kabart.

1614.name: Toruku's Letter
1614.description: A letter from Khavatari Toruku. Take this to Prefect Kasman.

1615.name: Khavatari Totem
1615.description: A token given to one who has qualifications to change occupations to Orc Monk. Take this to the high prefect to change your occupation to an Orc Monk.

1616.name: Fire Charm
1616.description: A charm with inscription of fire mantra. Take this and find the 3 items that Tataru spoke of.

1617.name: Kasha Bear Pelt
1617.description: A pelt of kasha bear. Take to Tataru along with kasha bladespider husk and fiery egg.

1618.name: Kasha Blade Spider Husk
1618.description: The husk of a kasha blade spider. Take it to Tataru, along with a kasha bear pelt and a fiery egg.

1619.name: 1st Fiery Egg
1619.description: A spirit egg obtained from a scarlet salamander. Take it to Tataru along with a kasha bear pelt and a kasha bladespider husk.

1620.name: Hestui Mask
1620.description: A mask in shape of bear. Take this and go to Hestui totem spirit.

1621.name: 2nd Fiery Egg
1621.description: A spirit egg received from a scarlet salamander. Take this to the Hestui totem spirit.

1622.name: Totem Spirit Claw
1622.description: A claw received from Hestui totem spirit. Take this and go to Tataru.

1623.name: Tataru's Letter of Recommendation
1623.description: A letter written by Tataru. Take this to Seer Umos in the town of Gludin.

1624.name: Flame Charm
1624.description: A charm with inscription of flame mantra. Take this and gather grizzly blood and take to Seer Umos.

1625.name: Grizzly Blood
1625.description: A glass bottle filled with grizzly blood. Gather 3 and take to Seer Umos.

1626.name: Blood Cauldron
1626.description: A cauldron filled with grizzly blood. Take this to the Duda-Mara totem spirit.

1627.name: Spirit Net
1627.description: A net made with Spirit's Spider Silk. Use this to capture Durka Spirit hidden inside Venomous Spiders.

1628.name: Bound Durka Spirit
1628.description: Durka spirit bound inside Spirit Net. Take this to the Duda-Mara totem spirit.

1629.name: Durka Parasite
1629.description: An evil parasite spirit that comes out from spiders contaminated with the evil durka spirit. It is the key for calling upon the evil durka spirit.

1630.name: Totem Spirit Blood
1630.description: Blood spilt by the Duda-Mara totem spirit. Take this and go to Seer Umos.

1631.name: Mask of Medium
1631.description: A token that shows one has the qualifications to become an Orc Shaman. Take this to the high prefect, to change your occupation to an Orc Shaman.

1632.name: Silvera's Ring
1632.description: A ring given to artisan aspirants by Blacksmith Silvera. Strike down the boogle ratman gang and collect their front teeth.

1633.name: 1st Pass Certificate
1633.description: The certificate for passing the 1st artisan test. To take the next test, you must go to Blacksmith Kluto of the village Gludin.

1634.name: 2nd Pass Certificate
1634.description: The certificate for passing the 2nd artisan test. Take this and go to Blacksmith Kluto in Gludin.

1635.name: Final Pass Certificate
1635.description: The certificate for passing the final Artisan test. Take this to the head blacksmith to change occupations to an Artisan.

1636.name: Boogle Ratman Tooth
1636.description: The ugly front bucktooth of a boogle ratman. Just looking at it will make you nauseous. Collect 10 of these and take them to Blacksmith Silvera.

1637.name: Boogle Ratman Leader's Tooth
1637.description: The boogle ratman leader's big tooth. Before its stink makes you pass out, collect 2 of them and take them to Blacksmith Silvera.

1638.name: Kluto's Letter
1638.description: Blacksmith Kluto's letter. Take to Blacksmith Pinter in the Town of Gludio.

1639.name: Footprint of Thief
1639.description: Trace left by thieves. Kill Vuku Orc fighters, recover stolen items and take them to Blacksmith Pinter.

1640.name: Stolen Secret Box
1640.description: A secret box stolen by Vuku orc fighters. The contents of the box are unknown, but anyway, take it to Blacksmith Pinter.

1641.name: Secret Box
1641.description: A secret box received from Pinter. The contents are unknown, but do not worry and take it to Blacksmith Kluto in the Village of Gludin.

1642.name: Ring of Raven
1642.description: A mark certifying that one has earned the right to become a Scavenger. If you take it to a Warehouse Chief, you can transfer your class to Scavenger.

1643.name: Pippi's Letter of Recommendation
1643.description: A letter of introduction written by Collector Pipi. Take this to Trader Mion.

1644.name: Raut's Teleport Scroll
1644.description: An order sheet given by Warehouse Freightman Raut. Give it to Torai, in the south of Death Pass.

1645.name: Succubus Undies
1645.description: The underwear of Succubus received from Torai. Take this to Warehouse Freightman Raut of Gludin.

1646.name: Mion's Letter
1646.description: A letter sent from Trader Mion to her brother. Take this letter and go to Master Toma.

1647.name: Bronk's Ingot
1647.description: An ingot to be given to Chief Blacksmith Bronk.

1648.name: Shari's Axe
1648.description: An axe to be given to Trader Shari.

1649.name: Zimenf's Potion
1649.description: A potion to give to Priest of the Earth Zimenf.

1650.name: Bronk's Pay
1650.description: Product cost given by Chief Blacksmith Bronk. Take this to Trader Mion.

1651.name: Shari's Pay
1651.description: Product cost given by Shari. Take this to Trader Mion.

1652.name: Zimenf's Pay
1652.description: Product cost given by Zimenf. Take this to Trader Mion.

1653.name: Bear Picture
1653.description: A picture of a bear received by Master Toma. Take this to hunt hunter bears, then the honey bear will appear.

1654.name: Tarantula Picture
1654.description: A picture of spider received by Master Toma. Use this to hunt tarantulas.

1655.name: Honey Jar
1655.description: A honey jar taken from a honey bear. Collect 5 and take them to Master Toma.

1656.name: Bead
1656.description: A bead obtained from tarantula. Gather 20 of these and give to Master Toma.

1657.name: Bead Parcel
1657.description: A parcel made of beads. Give this to Warehouse Freightman Raut of Gludin.

1658.name: Gatekeeper Charm
1658.description: Used to teleport from the Orc Village to Gludin.

1659.name: Gatekeeper Token
1659.description: Used to teleport from the Dwarven Village to Gludin.

1660.name: Cursed Maingauche
1660.description: Cursed Maingauche. Although its P. Atk. is weak, it gives bleeding effect with a certain rate during a critical attacks.

1662.name: Wood
1662.description: A material used to make Dwarven items. Can be sold in any shop.

1663.name: (Not In Use) Trunk
1663.description: A material used to make Dwarven items. Can be sold in any shop.

1664.name: Steel Powder
1664.description: A material used to make Dwarven items. Can be sold in any shop.

1665.name: World Map
1665.description: An ancient, obsolete map. Can be purchased at any shop.

1666.name: Recipe: Wooden Arrow
1666.description: For Dwarves only. The recipe for a Wooden Arrow. Requires Create Item Level 1. The success rate is 100%.

1667.name: Spellbook: Summon Shadow
1667.description: Spellbook needed to learn Summon Shadow. Used by Dark Wizards. Required level: 20

1668.name: Spellbook: Summon Mew the Cat
1668.description: Spellbook needed to learn Summon Mew the Cat. Used by Human Wizards. Required level: 20

1669.name: Spellbook: Summon Boxer the Unicorn
1669.description: Spellbook needed to learn Summon Boxer the Unicorn. Used by Elven Wizards. Required level: 20

1670.name: Spellbook: Summon Mirage the Unicorn
1670.description: Spellbook needed to learn Summon Mirage the Unicorn. Used by Elven Wizards. Required level: 20

1671.name: Spellbook: Summon Silhouette
1671.description: Spellbook needed to learn Summon Silhouette. Used by Dark Wizards. Required level: 20
